commitResults.messageBody: Users can mark a flashcard as reviewed by inputting reviewed [index]. The review status is displayed beside the flashcard name when 'list' command is called.
Users can now set the priority of a task using priority [taskIdx] [priorityLevel]. Exception handling has not been fully implemented for this.
Small adjustments to make code more readable and organized.

commitResults.messageBody: Made priorityLevel an enum with HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW and DEFAULT (not indicated) options. Added Javadoc comments to some command classes.

commitResults.messageBody: Users can now use either list-group [groupName] or list-group [groupIdx] to show the flashcards in the group.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add getShortDescription method for all flashcards and edit timeline
commitResults.messageBody: Timeline now shows only a short description instead of all flashcard details. Easier for user to get an overview of the flashcards.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add restricted period feature to timeline
commitResults.messageBody: Users can type "timeline [startdate: DD-MM-YYYY] [enddate: DD-MM-YYYY]" to restrict timeline listings to this period (inclusive of start and end dates) only.
